Description: Pottery transport amphora, about a half preserved. Heavy lip and flat handles. Red dipinto on shoulder.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Great Temenos, Vicinity (outside) of the north-west corner (Hogarth excavations 1903)
Curator's comments: The amphora would seem to be fifth century, not earlier, but few details are available to judge.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JA.086)
